question: In which nation "Jardines de la Reina" archipelago is located?
explanation: Jardines de la Reina archipelago is located on the southern coast of Cuba facing the Caribbean Sea. It houses one of Cuba's largest protected areas, Jardines de la Reina National Park and Marine Reserve. It is Cuba's second-largest archipelago, smaller only than Jardines del Rey. One part of this archipelago is known as then "The Labyrinth of the Twelve Leagues".
